# Image Services

Images services are used to upload and display pictures. Please read this documentation carefully before implementing any features that requires picture upload.

## Uploading Pictures

```shell
curl --location --request POST 'https://ms-image-v1.cheapreats.com/upload' \
--header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
--data-raw '{
	"image": "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
}'
```

```javascript
CE.Image.upload("data:image/jpeg;base64,")
    .then(result => {
        console.log(`Image ID is ${result.id}`);
    });
```

To upload a picture, you have to pass in a base64 encoded image data. It must include proper base64 headers as shown in the code example.

The result will contain an image ID and a few links to images. You want to keep the ID, links are only for debugging purposes.


<aside class="notice">
You must keep track of the image ID, under <b>no circumstances</b> you should ever directly store the image links.
</aside>

## Displaying Pictures

```javascript
const link = CE.Image.getLink(
    "60ec5ab6-37dd-4f20-8203-1b3fc2fac1d1",
    "100px"
);
```

To display a picture, assuming you already have the image ID available, there is a fancy SDK method you can use to obtain the proper HTTP link to the image. See code sample for details.

The second parameter is the image size you want to get, there are a few available:

* 100px
* 300px
* 600px
* 1200px
